    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="463"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760c.61/266</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geddes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 550</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour, on instructions from my
                    Government, to inform you that an adequate British Naval force is being
                    dispatched to Dantzig to afford such assistance as may be possible to the High
                    Commissioner with a view to securing Poland’s communications with the sea, in
                    accordance with Article 104 of the Treaty of Versailles which secures Poland’s
                    free and unrestricted use of the port of Dantzig. I understand that the French
                    Government are also dispatching a Naval force with the same end in view.</p>
                <p>I am instructed, in concert with my French and Italian colleagues who are, I
                    understand, submitting a similar request,<note n="23" xml:id="d463fn23">Similar
                        French and Italian representations not found in Department files.</note> to
                    ask that orders may be issued to the Naval forces of the United States to
                    collaborate in the maintenance of order at the port of Dantzig, having
                    particular regard to the effect which American collaboration cannot fail to
                    produce on the population of that port.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>(For H. M. Ambassador)<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Maurice Peterson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
